# Core Workflow

## Navigation (entry points, in order)
1. Read `PROJECT_STATUS.md` FIRST — current state, decisions, parameters, next steps.
2. Grep `CODE_INDEX.md` to locate a symbol's file + line (never read it in full).
3. Open `docs/Documentation.md` only when you need API/algorithm rationale.
- Infer purpose from names/paths/imports before opening files; read targeted ranges in large files (`shared/wmo_algorithms.js`, `legacy-ui/*` are big).
- Never recursive-glob the whole repo just to "explore". `legacy/`, `public/test-algo/`, `docs/icones WMO/` are archives — ignore unless asked.

## Safety
- NEVER delete files unless the user explicitly confirms.
- NEVER `git add` / `commit` / `push` without explicit user approval.
- Use `// TODO:` only when justified with clear context.

## Autonomy
- For reversible choices (naming, formatting, defaults, equivalent approaches), pick a reasonable option and note it instead of asking.
- Ask only for scope changes, ambiguous requirements, or destructive actions.
- When interpretations differ, prefer maintainability, scalability, low technical debt.

## After modifying files
- If you create/rename/delete a file or an export, or change behavior/APIs/algorithms → the on-demand `doc-and-logs` rule applies (update STATUS/INDEX/docs and tick the backlog item).
